                     <t:list xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#176">-176</locus>
                           <desc>Loose folio</desc>
                           <q xml:lang="ar">بسم الله الرحمن الرحيم الحمد لله على ما الهما ومنّ من تعليمه وفهما ثم صلا سلاه الله بر الجلال على النبي المصطفى والال سالتني عما به تدين وما الذي تاركه...</q>
                           <note/>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#Upper pastedown">-Upper pastedown</locus>
                           <desc>Book loan / transaction</desc>
                           <q xml:lang="en">THE SOCIETY OF FRIENDS OF THE INSITUTE OF ETHIOPIA STUDIES 
Has donated this book to the library of the institute.
Date: March 9 2007</q>
                           <q xml:lang="am"/>
                           <note>The same content is repeated in Amharic; there is also the watermark (almost unreadable) of the IES; printed piece of paper glued to the cover, with the date handwritten in blue ballpoint.</note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <locus target="#175">-175</locus>
                           <desc>Loose folio</desc>
                           <q>Different notes: one mentions al-Suyūṭī; another is a formula of istiġfār;</q>
                           <note>Small piece of paper, cut on the edges; all the texts are only partially readable.</note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a4">
                           <locus target="#1v-2v">-1v-2v</locus>
                           <desc>Fawā'id and masā'il</desc>
                           <q>Different fawā'id about: rite to preserve the whole body from any kind of illness; verses of the Quran not suitable to make "magic shares"; analysis of the words pronounced during the tašahhud at the end of the ritual prayer (quoting al-Šaʿrānī); ruḫṣa and taḫfīf (quoting al-Baġawī).</q>
                           <note/>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a5">
                           <locus target="#1r">-1r</locus>
                           <desc>Fawā'id and masā'il</desc>
                           <q>Different fawā'id about sight and rising of the moon;</q>
                           <note>Text almost faded away and partially covered by the binding.</note>
                        </item>
